glossary: having or covered with protective barbs or quills or spines or thorns or setae etc.; "a horse with a short bristly mane"; "bristly shrubs"; "burred fruits"; "setaceous whiskers"
containing an unusual amount of grease or oil; "greasy hamburgers"; "oily fried potatoes"; "oleaginous seeds"
of or relating to whales and dolphins etc
resembling or covered with wax; "as shiny as a waxy pippin"; "the ceraceous surface of the leaves"
